s":[{"name":"O'Donnell","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Brigid, Niall, Siobhan, Brennan, Bridie, Declan, Donal, Fergus, Jarlath, John Patrick, Padraic.","Irish (Donegal, Munster): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Domhnaill</b> ‘descendant of <i>Domhnall</i>’, an old personal name composed of the Celtic elements <i>domno-</i> ‘world’ + <i>val-</i> ‘might, rule’. Compare the Anglicized form   Donald   and the Scottish clan name   McDonald  .","History: The O'Donnells, like the O'Neills (see   O'Neill  ), claim descent from Niall of the Nine Hostages (Niall Noígíallach), a legendary 5th-century king of Ireland. Their traditional base is Tyrconnell (i.e. Donegal)."],"variants":[{"name":"O'Donell","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Donnell  ."]},{"name":"O'Donnel","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Donnell  ."]},{"name":"O'Daniel","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Donnell  , influenced by the Biblical name   Daniel  , to which it is etymologically unrelated."]},{"name":"O'Donald","meanings":["Irish: Scotticized form of   O'Donnell  . The Irish personal name <i>Domhnall</i> was Latinized as <i>Donaldus</i>, which is the source of <i>Donald</i>, the form of the personal name used in English in Scotland, though not in Ireland. The form <i>O'Donald</i> is therefore a 19th-century hybrid. Compare   Donald  ."]},{"name":"Donald","meanings":["Scottish: shortened form of   McDonald   (<i>Mac Dhomhnaill</i>), from the Gaelic personal name <i>Domhnall</i>; found in 13th- and 14th-century Scotland as <i>Dofnald</i>, <i>Douenald</i>, <i>Dufenald</i>, and <i>Donald</i>.","Irish (Ulster): possibly also a shortened and altered form of Irish   O'Donell  ."]}]},{"name":"Gormley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Aileen, Brigid, Declan, Eamonn, Nuala.","Irish (Tyrone): shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Gormghaile</b> ‘descendant of <i>Gormghal</i>’, a personal name from <i>gorm</i> ‘noble, dark blue’ + <i>gal</i> ‘valor’."],"variants":[{"name":"Gromley","meanings":["Irish: possibly a metathesized form of   Gormley  ."]},{"name":"Ghormley","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Gormley  ."]},{"name":"Gormly","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Gormley  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Gormley O'Donnell was born in 1360, in County Tyrone, Ireland as the daughter of John O'Donnell and Mrs. John O'Donnell. She married Niall Mór \"The Big\" O'Neill - of Tyrone about 1387, in Ireland. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. She died in 1397, in her hometown, at the age of 37."},"et":{"1360–1397":"1360–1397","1340–1397":"1340–1397","1388–1429":"1388–1429","–1416":"–1416","1338–Male":"1338–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1338":"1338","1388":"1388","1397":"1397","1340":"1340","about 1387":"umbes 1387","1360":"1360","about 1388":"umbes 1388","1429":"1429","1416":"1416","Tyrone, Ireland":"County Tyrone, Iirimaa","Ireland":"Iirimaa"},"fi":{"1360–1397":"1360–1397","1340–1397":"1340–1397","1388–1429":"1388–1429","–1416":"–1416","1338–Male":"1338–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1338":"1338","1388":"1388","1397":"1397","1340":"1340","about 1387":"noin 1387","1360":"1360","about 1388":"noin 1388","1429":"1429","1416":"1416","Tyrone, Ireland":"County Tyrone, Irlanti","Ireland":"Irlanti"},"fr":{"1360–1397":"1360–1397","1340–1397":"1340–1397","1388–1429":"1388–1429","–1416":"–1416","1338–Male":"1338–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1338":"1338","1388":"1388","1397":"1397","1340":"1340","about 1387":"environ 1387","1360":"1360","about 1388":"environ 1388","1429":"1429","1416":"1416","Tyrone, Ireland":"County Tyrone, Irlande","Ireland":"Irlande","lifeSummary":"Gormley O'Donnell est née en 1360, à County Tyrone, Irlande, fille de John O'Donnell et Mrs. John O'Donnell. Elle a épousé Niall Mór \"The Big\" O'Neill - of Tyrone environ 1387, à Irlande. Il